    "Quantum Mob/ Q3 Symbol", "language" -> "en", "paclet" -> "QuantumMob/Q3",
     "status" -> "None", "summary" -> 
    "RandomCliffordCircuitSimulate[in, {n, depth, ds}, spec] simulates \
Clifford circuits randomly generated by RandomCliffordCircuit[in, {n, depth}, \
spec], and collects a state at every ds layers for each run of Clifford \
quantum circuits. RandomCliffordCircuitSimulate[in, {n, depth}, spec] is \
equivalent to RandomCliffordCircuitSimulate[in, {n, t, 3}, spec], that is, \
collects states only at the measurement/decoherence layers. \
RandomCliffordCircuitSimulate[{n, depth}, spec] or \
RandomCliffordCircuitSimulate[{n, depth, ds}, spec] assumes the conventional \
initial state Ket[{0, 0, ...}].", "synonyms" -> {}, "tabletags" -> {}, 
    "title" -> "RandomCliffordCircuitSimulate", "titlemodifier" -> "", 
    "metadescription" -> "", "windowtitle" -> "RandomCliffordCircuitSimulate",
